<法規>
<法規性質>命令</法規性質>
<英文法規名稱>Regulation on Nutrition-Labeling for Packaged Vitamin and Mineral Tablets and Capsules on the Market</英文法規名稱>
<中文法規名稱>市售包裝維生素礦物質類之錠狀膠囊狀食品營養標示方式及內容標準</中文法規名稱>
<法規網址>http://law.moj.gov.tw/Eng/LawClass/LawContent.aspx?PCODE=L0040090</法規網址>
<最新英文異動日期>20130910</最新英文異動日期>
<廢止註記>廢</廢止註記>
<沿革內容><![CDATA[1.Promulgated on Novenber 29, 2010
2.Amended on September 10, 2013
3.Abolished on January 01, 2016]]></沿革內容>
<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This standard is established under the provisions of Item 2 of Article 22 of the Act Governing Food Sanitation.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Packaged vitamin and mineral tablets and capsules on the market shall provide the following information shown at a conspicuous place of the outer package or container:
(1)     Title of “Nutrition labeling”
(2)     Vitamin contents
(3)     Mineral contents
(4)     Contents of other ingredients labeled by the manufacturer voluntarily
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Ways of labeling of contents of vitamins, minerals and other ingredients: The contents of each tablet (or capsule) shall be labeled and the number of tablets (or capsules) contained in each package of the product and the daily value (in percentage) provided by each tablet (or capsule) shall be specified. Where no daily value is established with respect to a certain ingredient, the daily value section shall be asterisked (*) and specify the following wording:”* Daily Value not established.”
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The contents of vitamins, minerals and other ingredients shall be labeled in metric units. For Vitamins A, D and E, the contents shall be additionally labeled in IU.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
