  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Rule of rounding-off: The number of tablets (or capsules) in each package and the percentage of daily value shall be expressed in integer. The contents of vitamins, minerals and other ingredients shall be expressed in not more than three significant figures.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 7</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[If the physiological functions of packaged vitamin and mineral tablets and capsules on the market are to be described, the minimum daily intake must be 15% of the daily value.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 8</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Packaged vitamin and mineral tablets and capsules on the market shall label the following warning at a conspicuous place: “No more thantablets (or capsules) each day.”
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 9</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[“The Standard of the Format and Covering Items on Nutrition Labeling for Prepackaged Foods” shall not apply to packaged vitamin and mineral tablets and capsules on the market.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 10</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The implementation date for this standard shallbeimplementedfromApril 30, 2012.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
